Title: Fast & Furious 8 - Official Trailer 1 (Universal Pictures) HD
Comment:
I am a big fan of movies about cars and have watched every Fast and Furious movie since I was a child. This movie is an action film and after the unfortunate death of one of the main actors Paul Walker it was clear the series will continue to be releasing action packed spin offs where the plot revolves around Dominic Toretto (Vin Diesel).
As it was already mentioned, the main story is about Dom. In this movie his ex-girlfriend and her child (Dom's son) are hijacked by a cyberterrorist who calls herself Cipher. Cipher gets Dom trapped and makes him a part of her team. Dom has to leave his ,,brothers'' who are the supposed ,,good guys'' which makes no sense either because they steal secret and expensive technologies such as an EMP from the military while still working for some secret police service. Dom can not reject joining the ,,bad guys'' because otherwise his son and ex-girlfriend will be killed by Cipher's ,,sharpshooters''(,the girlfriend is later killed). His original crew teams up with one of the most dangerous criminals in the world: Deckard Shaw (Jason Statham). Together they try to stop Cipher from possibly leading to something as bad as the end of the world while having no idea why Dom had left them. As expected, the film ends on a good note when Deckard saves Dom's child and Dom reunites with his squad, although Cipher manages to escape. 
The movie is not made for kids as it is not light-hearted. It includes a lot of violence, in some cases brutal. There are a lot of speical effects such as explosions which get too repetitive or boring towards the end because there are just too many of them, sometimes for no actual reason what so ever. It left like the movie was directed by Michael Bay while he was high on something and through the effect of some ,,chemical elements'' decided to add explosions everywhere. This thought-process reminds me of a small young boys' who just want to see crazy stuff happen around them. The stunts seemed epic and there were also some exotic locations if you consider Cuba and Siberia to be on this list.
Althought I would not rate this movie as one of my favourites, I will still continue to support the series because that is where it all started (petrolhead mania), what I mean by this is that we have to respect our roots. I would recommend this movie to every action movies fan as this one has no less explosions than any other one. (6/10- IGN)

Comment:
After watching the trailer in theatres I'm like... "They're still making this?" 

Okay here's the breakdown Donny turned bad for no apparently reason unless it's mind control or some random lazy plot device, Jason ( I forgot the character's name) joins with the main characters which why in the living hell would he join them when he killed that Asian guy from Tokyo Drift, their friend?! The villain is woman, probably she might make a film look good seeing its Charlize Theron as the antagonist but it won't. At Roman's humour hadn't died out, but it's going to be irritable hearing him freaking out and claiming himself to be dope. The Characters especially Letty taking about family this and family that "Ugh.. we get it, you don't to remind us every 5 mins!" A ton of action scenes which will attract some people seeing how they would fall for Michael Bay's inner ego putting that into a film. party dancing sexy woman which will make us perverts see the film, Muscular men like Dwayne Johnson and Vin Diesel will attract the female demographic, and a rap song which will build up the hype, and let's of course make this about racing which is only a spy movie that is completely out of the concept of racing. Since when racing became about fighting terrorist and making badass action scenes? The point of this franchise is the passion of racing, both competitively and respectfully which makes it outside the law to see that it's enjoyable and fun which sometimes get them into trouble. great arc which you all know about building up to that family and brotherhood, it was simple in the previous films, now look at this shit. Now even the most dedicated of actors could saved this franchise, the 7th film should've ended there, it was right, it was emotional, it was a perfect ending to a racing trilogy. And now it's going to decline. Or maybe it's still good, I don't know I'm really skeptical about this. I might see it, but it's probably gonna suck. I didn't any disrespect which I made to the actors, they're all good, and I'm not discouraging to see this film, this is just my opinion.

Comment:
Whether you prefer to take it in the spirit of sincerity or deadpan self-satire, the Fast & Furious franchise has for awhile now gotten a lot of mileage out of winking at the notion that the enduring car-stunt series is actually grounded in an earnest message about the importance of (as Dominic Toretto pronounces it) ‚ÄúFambly.‚Äù The post-biological band-of-brothers is framed as a group so tight-knit that it scarcely matters that no one can really pinpoint where they transitioned from drag-racing freeway-pirates to a sought-after anti-terrorism mercenary squad.

But the trailer for Part 8, The Fate of The Furious, debuted with a shocking twist: Patriarch Dominic Toretto has changed lanes to the Dark Side!

Obviously, fans were expecting something drastic to change about the franchise foundations for this kickoff to the purported trilogy of features set to bring the series to a definitive endpoint in Part 10. By now the series has done just about as much as can be done with the ‚Äúseries all-stars do a job‚Äù premise that‚Äôs been fueling the brand since Fast Five; and with onetime second-in-command Paul Walker having passed away tragically during the production of Furious 7, it was clear a new direction would be necessary.

But nobody could‚Äôve predicted a story shift as out-of-nowhere as what was revealed in the Fate of The Furious trailer; which opens with what initially looks like a mystery (‚ÄúToretto has gone rogue ‚Äì why?‚Äù) only to quickly reveal the big hook: Dom has fallen under the spell of Charlize Theron‚Äôs ‚ÄúCipher,‚Äù an international criminal mastermind who has turned him against his former teammates as part of a sinister global terrorism scheme. Not only is he working for a villain, they also appear to be an item ‚Äì which comes as a shock to Michelle Rodriguez as Toretto‚Äôs now cured-of-amnesia wife Letty.

Comment:
This COULD be a masterpiece with Diesel, Statham, Theron, Johnson and even without Walker, but I know it from now it will suck.. even from the trailer many months before premiere u can tell it. IT WILL SUCK :( 
Looks like the "2012" movie.. "enjoy the effects" but .......forget everything else !
Just like the Saw movies.. decided to end them in a three-set, changed their mind from when was too late and continued the franchise finding every way to make a story. Saw, from 3 to 7 movies, FF from 2+1extra (+1extra=Tokyo Drift) to 10... resulting a story that does not make sense to anyone with half brain but fits more in a comics magazine. Just like Lionsgate with Saw here we have Universal with Fast & Furious. two companies, two series that could be GREAT from the first to the last, two AMAZING first movies.. two "OK" second movies and then what? the same mistake. Making the third movie deciding "this will be the last one" and deciding to continue the series when it was too late to make it look good.
In this case and only from scenario point of view after Tokyo Drift. The FBI recruit and death of Letty, the "one last job" @ Rio, the resurrection of Letty for another "one last job", & "one last ride", with all that Dominic rides RX7 in #1, Han too in #3TD, and one month after Han's death there is a McLaren, a Veyron, a 458 along with the new Viper and the new SRT, and of course a Lycan HyperSport jumping 3 buildings (irrelevant at this point talking about cars, relevant if you think about the production of the cars and the word "continuity" though..) and is this orange Lambo in the trailer a Huracan? and in the trap I see a Merc GT/GTS or an SLS? 20+ mile highway with the airplane scene, everyone dies falling of the plane but Shaw.. OK, sorry but those make no sense but doesn't matter either, just because the list of mistake examples (and BIG mistakes in the case of FF series) is endless. Like I said, this will be an epic example of "enjoy the effects but forget everything else" and I don't like it being Fast&Furious fan until the sixth movie.. Surely I'm not the only one.
Doin' everything just to keep it going and for the millions of dollars of course..
Pity, pity.. pity.
Happy 2017 to all !

Comment:
So, before I start asking questions and theorising, I love the franchise, the characters and actors. 
In such a big franchise, they can't just ignore or forget Brian O'Connor (Paul Walker). It would be spitting at the fan base, followed by kicking, punching and destroying their souls and franchise in the face. 

Which leaves me with 3 theories:

POSSIBLE SPOILERS!!
1. Brian was killed either by Dom or by Charlize Theron's character which would be a gut wrenching twist.
2. Brian is the bait that Theron's character uses to make Dom do as she says.
3. He's retired with his family to a lovely farm far away from the chaos of F&F.

Personally I expected, and a small part of me wanted the franchise to end after Paul's awfully short departure. He was and is a pinnacle part of this family's franchise who will live on in our heart.

Whatever they end up doing, I hope they do what is right, both creatively and respectfully.

RIP Paul Walker.
